  - Supabase clients at `src/lib/supabase/client.ts` and `src/lib/supabase/server.ts`
  - Types at `src/lib/supabase/types.ts`
  - Middleware at `src/middleware.ts` (public paths: /login, /register, /scan, /)
  - `app/page.tsx` redirects to /login

- Route structure: route groups `(merchant)` and `(auth)` exist. Customer portal will use a `(customer)` route group.
- Since `app/page.tsx` exists and resolves to `/`, the customer pages MUST be under `(customer)/customer/` to get the URL `/customer` (same pattern as merchant which uses `(merchant)/merchant/page.tsx` → `/merchant`).

